         <abstract id="aspace_31e6a2f45b3b658462eab14a1a3c0ce0">The D.C. Rape Crisis Center was founded in 1972 as one of the first rape crisis centers in the country, and the only center at the time run primarily by and for women of color. This collection contains orientation information for new volunteers, as well as event information, various publications, and pamphlets.</abstract>
